-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Fri Dec 05, 2014 09:30AM EST
-- None



Dec 5 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1430 GMT on Friday:

** France's deal with India to sell 126 Rafale fighter jets in a transaction worth an estimated $15 billion will need several months more negotiations, French Defense Minister Jean-Yves Le Drian said on Friday. [ID:nL6N0TP0H9]  ** Songbird Estates <SBDE.L>, the owner of London's Canary Wharf financial district, has rejected a raised joint bid from Qatar's sovereign wealth fund and a North American investor that values the company at 2.6 billion pounds ($4.07 billion). [ID:nL6N0TP0K8]  ** British infrastructure group Balfour Beatty <BALF.L> said on Friday that it had rejected a 1 billion pound ($1.6 billion) offer from John Laing Infrastructure Fund <JLIF.L> for its public-private partnership assets. [ID:nFWN0TN05G]  ** Australian mining products maker Bradken Ltd <BKN.AX> said it was considering a cut-price $730 million takeover proposal from Bain Capital and Pacific Equity Partners, underscoring the urgency the sector faces amid plunging commodities prices. [ID:nL3N0TO5KU]  ** Austria's Takeover Commission has approved plans by Australia's IFM Investors to raise its offer for Vienna Airport <VIEV.VI> to 82 euros per share from 80 euros, IFM said on Friday. [ID:nL6N0TP0OY]  ** Italian tycoon Andrea Bonomi raised his takeover bid for Club Mediterranee <CMIP.PA> on Friday to 24 euros per share from 23 euros, leapfrogging the latest 23.50-euro offer for the French holiday group from Chinese billionaire Guo Guangchang. [ID:nL6N0TP1UU]  ** India's Reliance Industries Ltd <RELI.NS> said on Friday that it had entered a pact with Mexico's national oil company Petroleos Mexicanos (Pemex) [PEMX.UL] to explore potential upstream oil and gas business opportunities in that country. [ID:nL3N0TP1HD]  ** Chinese sovereign fund China Investment Corp (CIC) has sold its entire stake in Singapore-listed water treatment company SIIC Environment Holdings Ltd <SIIC.SI> for about S$98 million ($74.4 million) in a block share trade, IFR reported. [ID:nL3N0TP359]  ** Brazil's Vale SA <VALE5.SA> said on Friday it was in negotiations with an investor over the sale of a stake in its Mozambique coal assets, responding to reports it was selling the stake to Japanese trader Mitsui & Co <8031.T>. [ID:nL2N0TP0LU]  ** ICICI Bank Ltd <ICBK.NS>, India's biggest private sector lender, on Friday said it would sell its banking unit in Russia to mid-sized Russian bank, Sovcombank. [ID:nL3N0TP3SG]  ** China Shenhua Energy Co Ltd <601088.SS> will be part of a consortium bidding to develop the giant Mongolian coal project Tavan Tolgoi, the Chinese coal producer said on Thursday. [ID:nL3N0TP05J]